Good morning,
A new CGW GAP claim is enclosed for your review and consideration.
We have identified several discrepancies on this vehicle purchase/finance/GAP policy, summarized as follows:
The BOS indicates $20,695 for the vehicle, yet the finance contract shows $23,517.10.
The BOS indicates Protections for $4,745.35 before tax.  The finance contract indicates optional extended warranty for $2,450.  There should be a refund somewhere.
The BOS indicates $2,000 deposit where the finance contract shows $5,000. The GAP policy indicates $5,000 deposit.
The GAP policy shows premium of $2,250 that I don’t see on the BOS (premium or RST), and the finance contract shows $2,430 (no RST).
 These inconsistencies led our asking for the deposit receipt, of which only one could be produced for $1,000.  As indicated above, there is a refund to be confirmed on the warranty which will reduce the GAP benefit as currently calculated.
This client confirms Uber driving but the policy wording does not allow for decline unless the commercial insurer pays the loss.
We believe the inconsistencies in the documentation are sufficient grounds for denial.
Please review the file and let us know if any questions or your comments that result.
                                                        

Thank you,
Michael
